The paper discusses a formal model of the x86 instruction-set architecture and supports reasoning about x86 machine-code programs. This suggests that the paper is likely to belong to the Programming Languages (cs.PL), Architecture (cs.AR), Software Engineering (cs.SE), Logic in Computer Science (cs.LO), or Cryptography and Security (cs.CR) sub-categories.
